==English==
===Etymology===
[[kill]] + [[-er]]

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪlə(r)|-ɪlə(r)]]

===Noun===
'''killer''' ([[killers]])

#A person who [[kill]]s.
#A murderer.
#An animal that kills.
#Something that causes death.
#:''Driving while tired can be a '''killer'''.''
#A [[diacritic]] mark used in [[Indic]] scripts to suppress an inherent vowel.
#''Also used attributively''.

====Synonyms====
*1, 2: [[assassin]], [[murderer]]
*5: [[virama]], [[halant]]

